start.label: can't live with them can't live without them

examples.en: It's hopeless to expect him to help.
He is a hopeless romantic.
I began to feel lonely and hopeless.
I'm hopeless at mathematics.
I'm a hopeless cook.
I've got a hopeless memory.
We recognized that the situation was hopeless.
The situation is not as hopeless as it might seem.
My brother was always pretty hopeless at ball games.
You can't do a thing for people like that, they are hopeless.
I'm hopeless with machinery.
It is hopeless trying to screen your child from the harmful effects of television.
She was a hopeless romantic, always convinced that one day she would meet the man of her dreams.
The situation grew increasingly hopeless.
He's very ill, but his condition isn't hopeless.
The firm had to charge off the debt as hopeless.
I'd love to get rid of my infatuation for Jane; it's all hopeless.
The facts add together to give a hopeless picture of the firm's future.
Jim's plan seemed hopeless, but he brought it off.
The public transport system was absolutely hopeless.
Getting your work published often seems a hopeless task.
It was a hopeless love that could not possibly be reciprocated.
I kept on struggling forward, even though I knew it was hopeless.
You cannot blind yourself to the true facts; the position is hopeless.
We tried to stop the flames from spreading, but we knew it was hopeless.
In the process of taking down the Christmas tree, we managed to entangle the string of lights into a hopeless mess of wires.
